Eastern Cape Health MEC Sindiswa Gomba says 102 learners, one teacher and 15 members of the Burgersdorp community have tested positive for COVID-19. Courtesy of #DStv403 BURGERSDORP - The Burgersdorp community has been hit hard by COVID-19. Eastern Cape Health MEC Sindiswa Gomba said 102 learners, one teacher and 15 members of the community have tested positive for COVID-19. READ: Level 1: Mkhize warns COVID-19 battle is not over All the people who have tested positive for the virus are in isolation. "Health teams have been placed in the same places to monitor their symptoms," Gomba said. A team of experts and tracers have been deployed to the province following this outbreak. READ: COVID-19 in SA: PPE shortages in Eastern Cape hospitals The MEC said her department is working with the Department of Education to control infections. Watch the video above for more on this story.   - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.